I once got French onion soup from a popular chain restaurant and nearly cried from how badly they ruined it. It was bland and had a weird texture. Compared to other French onion soup I've had, it was like they'd only heard the name "French onion soup" and just kinda... put some onions in some bland stock and put cheese on top. Not one part of it was appetizing.
My dad used to make a variation on it when I was little and it was so warm and delicious and comforting. This one looks more like that.
